ple of 8 spells:<br>
<br>
Burst of Flame lvl 1<br>
Burst of Fire lvl 5<br>
Ignite lvl 9<br>
Combust lvl 29<br>
Firestrike lvl 39<br>
Starfire lvl 49<br>
Wildfire lvl 59<br>
Summer's Flame lvl 64<br>
<br>
I'll give you 3 guesses what they have in common. They are all fire dd spells. Each spell simply an upgrade of the one before it. I think the death of original spells came with Kunark. Wake of Karana, Call of Hero, Divine Intervention, Mark of Karn, etc. Nothing earth shattering. But at least they provided variety and new specialization to certain classes. Like druids became king of fire/cold resists. I want to see one original and useful spell come out for each class.<br>
<br>
I'm just pulling these out of my arse, but here are a few examples:<br>
<br>
Temporal Flux<br>
Class: Wizard<br>
Mana: 50<br>
Level: 63<br>
Cast Time: Instant<br>
Recast: 20 minutes<br>
Effect: This is difficult to explain so bear with me. Upon casting this spell the wizard jumps ten seconds into the future for ten seconds. The effects of this can be devastating. Upon casting the spell, the wizard will disappear from the site of the world for 10 seconds. After the 10 seconds are over, 2 wizards will be present. Each will be capable of a strategic event, both nuking same target, both run different directions etc. After the next 10 seconds are over there will only be one wizard present. The two wizards are in fact the same wizard. The way this would work in game would be after casting Temporal Flux the player would blink a random direction 10 ft away or so and the game world would freeze on the player's PC. The player has 10 seconds to do anything he likes, but none of the effects of his spells casted would take place... yet. After the 10 seconds are over he would reappear where he was 10 seconds ago, but the world would be in it's present state. A double of himself would appear and do exactly what he did during the 10 seconds the game world was frozen. Any damage done to the double will apply to the wizard because the double is in essence the wizard. Any spells cast by the double will be taken out of the wizards mana pool. If the double targets and nukes a target that died during the 10 seconds, then the mana is wasted from the wizard still. This is a double edged sword, while the wizard could do untold damage during the 10 seconds where he has a clone of himself, he is also twice as vulnerable to rampage etc. I understand this might be difficult to code, but I certainly believe it's possible.<br>
<br>
Frozen Time<br>
Class: Wizard<br>
Level: 59<br>
Mana: 500<br>
Cast: 2 seconds<br>
Duration: 45 seconds<br>
Recast: 10 minutes<br>
Limitation: Cannot cast spells or zone<br>
Effect: The wizard disappears, locked in time. The wizard can move freely for 45 seconds until time catches up. This spell is designed as a quick escape, or travel through dangerous area spell.<br>
<br>
Ethereal Nature Form<br>
Class: Druid<br>
Mana: 300<br>
Level: 62<br>
Limit: Outdoor Only<br>
Effect: The druid takes on the form of a spirit. (same model, but with white texture and see through). While in this form the druid can not cast any spells, but will also have nuetral faction to virtually all npc's. <br>
<br>
Tashania's Body Double<br>
Class: Enchanter<br>
Mana: 250<br>
Level: 58<br>
Cast time: Instant<br>
Recast: 35 minutes<br>
Effect: The enchanter creates an illusion of herself while simutaneously teleporting herself a random direction 30ft or so away while invising herself. In essence whatever was attacking the enchanter will think it successfully kills the enchanter, while she sneeks away invisible. The body double will have the same HP/AC the enchanter had at the time of the casting. The body double will continuously cast a hate increasing buff upon herself. The body double is incapable of doing any damage and will despawn in 5 minutes if not destroyed.<br>
<br>
Aid of the Arch-Magi<br>
Class: Mage<br>
Level: 62<br>
Mana: 100<br>
Cast: 5 seconds<br>
Effect: Think reverse CoH. The mage summons himself to someone in his group. This spell holds alot of obvious problems for designers. Think how easy it would be for a SoS rogue to go deep in a dungeon, the mage summons himself to the rogue once he gets in a safe spot and then summons the rest of the group/raid. If developers used this one, they would obviously have to limit the zones it could be used in, or come up with creative deterents. Outside a couple abuses, it could be a very fun spell for mages. no component, low mana.<br>
<br>
Unfailing Burning Hands<br>
Class: Mage<br>
Level: 64<br>
Mana: 500<br>
Cast: 5.5 seconds<br>
Effect: Mage summons himself to a line of site target and cast a 2100 fire lure dd. (think teleport and high damage burning hands in D&amp;D) The mana cost is justified by making it such a high risk spell. It also allows the mage to come up with some interesting tactics.<br>
<br>
Glyph of the Holy Servant<br>
Class: Cleric<br>
Level: 64<br>
Mana: 400<br>
Cast: 6 seconds<br>
Recast: 10 minutes<br>
Effect: The cleric summons a holy symbol that floats stationary above the ground. The symbol is visible to everyone and is inactive for 30 seconds. While it's visible it can be easily destroyed. After the 30 seconds are up, it is only visible to the cleric. (in pvp successful detect traps skill check makes it visible) Anyone who comes close to the symbol will activate the trap. The Glyph explodes with an AE stun effect. The stun is near impossible to resist and last 10 seconds. The cleric can only have one glyph up at a time. The explosion of the clerics glyph will destroy any other cleric glyphs in the area of effect. The glyph will despawn 30 minutes after casting. No material component necessary<br>
<br>
Glyph of the Oracle<br>
Class: Shaman<br>
Level: 64<br>
Mana: 500<br>
Cast: 6 seconds<br>
Recast: 10 minutes<br>
Effect: This spell is similar in nature to the cleric version. The only real difference is the shaman version will cast a powerful disease dot (breath of ulthor or something similar) on a single target that activated the glyph.<br>
<br>
Call of the corpse:<br>
Class: Necromancer<br>
Mana: 200<br>
Cast: 6 seconds<br>
Recast: 2 minutes<br>
Effect: The necromancer summons himself to a targeted corpse (PC or NPC).<br>
<br>
Enslavement of the Soul<br>
Class: Necromancer<br>
Level: 63<br>
Mana: 400<br>
Cast: 4 seconds<br>
Recast: 2.5 seconds<br>
Effect: The necromancer can attempt to forge a soul gem used for rezzing from a targeted NPC's coprse. 80% chance of failure. This allows the necromancer alternative means of acquiring soul gems. NPC corpses must be level 55+ <br>
<br>
Corpse Explosion<br>
Class: Necromancer<br>
Level: 62<br>
Mana: 400<br>
Cast: 5 seconds<br>
Recast: 2.5 seconds<br>
Effect: The corpse of a targetted NPC corpse explodes causing 1000 dd in the area of effect. The corpse that was exploded cannot be looted.  Corpses with magic items cannot be exploded.<br>
<br>
Mass Death Peace<br>
Class: Necromancer<br>
Mana: 500<br>
Cast Time: 3 seconds<br>
Recast: 15 minutes<br>
Component: Peridot<br>
Effect: Group Feign Death. This spell would give much more groupability to necros, as well as enhance their raid effectiveness.<br>
<br>
Mana Feedback<br>
Class: Shadowknight<br>
Level: 63<br>
Mana: 350<br>
Cast: 2 seconds<br>
Recast: 5 minutes<br>
Effect: The targetted pc/npc loses up to 500 mana. Any mana drained will cause 1.5 times as much life lost.<br>
<br>
Ranger- self only ports to druid locations at added mana and cast time.<br>
<br>
Translocate Self<br>
All Casting Hybrids<br>
Level: 58<br>
Mana: 600<br>
Cast Time: 20 seconds<br>
Recast Time: 1 minute<br>
Effect: Hybrid version of gate<br>
<br>
Valiant Guard<br>
Class: Paladin<br>
Level: 63<br>
Mana: 300<br>
Cast Time: 2 seconds<br>
Recast: 10 minutes<br>
Duration: 20 seconds<br>
Effect: The paladin will absorb 125% all damage done to the beneficiary of the spell. The beneficiary can not benefit from another Valiant Guard for 5 minutes after receiving this buff.<br>
<br>
