<br>
While I agree that the vast majority of spells in EQ are not original to eachother, and that a little more variety would certainly be a very good thing, I don't believe you have thought alot of your ideas through, with the wizard ideas being top of the list.<br>
<br>
<br>
Here are some Ideas I think could be looked into-- I make no claims on proper classes, though some obviously have a bent to one class or another.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Utter Concentration</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->--  Buff that locks the recipient in place, and causes all spells to be un-interuptible for the duration.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Know Terrain</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->-- Spell that instantly maps out for your minimap the zone for 500' in all directions.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Transport</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->-- Spell that pops up a dialouge, asking for a Loc, then sends you to the location of your choice within the zone.  Only works in outdoor, non-planar zones.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>7 League Boots</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->-- a tradecraftable or summoned pair of boots that gives Sow speed.  Boots have no stats however, so there is a trade off. Possibly might not work indoors.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Know Allies</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->-- Spell that gives a list of the targets positive factions.  A second spell in this line might provide all negative faction hits provided by the mob. Usefull for knowing before you kill a mob what hits you will take.  A third variety might provide all mobs or factions the target will assist in battle.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Bloodbond</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->-- Links caster and target so that a percentage of all damage take by the caster is instead applied to the target.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Temporal Stasis</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->-- Freezes a target in time for 30 seconds, making it unable to move, attack, and makes it invunerable for the duration.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Force Wall/Summon Wall</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->-- creates a targetable wall that can be destroyed directly in front of the caster.  Wall will break LOS for spells, mobs will stop to bash it down rather than pass by it unless there is a way around, ect...   HP and AC of the wall would depend on the effect desired, with Summon:Wooden Wall having perhaps 500hp and an AC of around 400, Summon:Brick Wall 4000Hp and 800ac, Summon:Stone Wall 10000hp and 1500ac--- or Ice Wall 5pt damage sheild with same stats as wood, Force Wall 15pt damage sheild with stats as Brick, and Wall of Fire being like Stone Wall, with 30pt damage sheild. If possible, in the energy version, only creatures able to hit magic can damage the wall, and a dispell will bring them down instantly...   <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>This idea might strain the engine however, I do freely admit.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Pierce the Veil</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->--  The target enters into the spirit world, becoming completly invisable to the living.  Those in the spirit world are still fully visable to undead, and may interact with undead normally without the living being alerted to the targets presence.  An alternate version could be <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Protection from Undead</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, doing the same thing only vs undead mobs.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>As a personal note, I believe either or both of these spells to be perfect for Clerics and Necromancers. Possibly the first form of invis I've seen yet that actually makes sense for clerics in fact.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Chaos of Zek</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->-- Buff that gives a percentage chance of any incomming damage to reflect to the attacker or an ally of the attacker instead of hitting the recipient.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Gift of 1000 hands</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->-- gives a percentage chance for additional attacks to be carried out with each swing.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Jump</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->-- Radically increases the height that a character can jump, and reduces falling damage.  Disabled in zones where you don't want rocketeers circumventing content, while allowing an alternative to gate when leaving Kaesora or similar dungeons.<br>
<br>
Gatestone-- creates a portal stone that lasts for 30 seconds.  Any who click on the gatestone are sent to the location that goes with the spell, for instance Gatestone of the North would send you to North Karana, Gatestone of Knowledge would send you to PoK, Gatestone of the Soul would send you to your Bind...<br>
<br>
Warded Invisablity-- Same as invisabilty, except that any creature breaks the invisablity is hit by a massive nuke.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>This would probably need either expensive reagents,long recast, or to be written off as a bad idea as I can think of lots of ways to exploit this. Probably not so bad if Nuke is replaced with auto-mez or snare/root instead.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
