<br>
In any case, those spells were designed with a penalty in mind and to negate that would make them VERY overpowering - the reagents aren't incredibly hard to come by but difficult enough that one would conserve the gems (imagine the solo'ing possiblities if you could zap yourself to FM with a reagent off a mob you just killed).<br>
<br>
Group FD - they tried to give bards this, it totally would have broken all existing content as most content relies on a concentration of aggro in one place and finding ways to keep it off of others (such as emp and tallon with de-aggroing debuffs.).  Overpowered, never work.<br>
<br>
Time shifts - not feasible within the engine, the closest they've come to this is the way Saryrn splits and that's because they can design the area and the encounter specifically so that it's always the same.  When dealing with PC's, nothing is constant and there'd be no way for the game to compensate, even if it was just an illusion.<br>
<br>
