Unless there are changes made, the grouping thing is a lesser option, the kiting thing is more difficult than what a Necromancer would have to do to solo.  The fact that there are some really talented wizards at kiting makes it more difficult for those who want to group &quot;Ahh, he can solo, why is he LFG?&quot;<br>
<br>
Which again I say good for them!  I wish I had that talent.<br>
<br>
So my suggestions were merely this. Give wizards some value added abilities for groups and raids.  I ask, would a nightmare bane give you more of a chance to get a group in nightmare if the spell were powerful enough and unresistable?  I think so.<br>
<br>
It's great to make me a master of the elements, but I get resists in PoP on high level malo'ed low ice resist creatures from Ice Spear than should be.  Verant's solution to this was to say &quot;Be in Melee range&quot; but then give me 3800 hitpoints fully buffed on a creature that quads for 1100 with a very low AC and I am one dead wizard.  But the only way I am going to land that spell is to get close...get aggro and die, even after 50% of it's health is gone, or to lose out to a massive AoE that debuffs and strips your epic rune.  I simply can't mitigate that kind of damage well.  At least, a Necromancer can FD.  At least a mage can sick the pet on the mob and have enough time to gate.<br>
<br>
And I have yet to meet one Enchanter who says &quot;Boy, do I have a hard time finding groups!&quot;<br>
<br>
And I am not a fool, I realise that everyone has their issues with their classes, but the question is that of what value do wizards add to grouping situation other than the unseeable direct damage?  In my 3 years of playing, it is rare to meet a person who truly sees this benefit.<br>
<br>
Really, like what was said.  We Evac, Translocate, and do Direct Damage, but I don't want a group simply because I can Evac, that's silly.  I want a group because they can use a massive amount of DPS, and even that in comparison to some other classes is negligable in the eyes of many players.<br>
<br>
And the concussion spells are a joke, level 39 spell that is very difficult to get and is ruined if you are a dark elf trying to get your epic, for example.<br>
<br>
Ancient: Greater Concussion?  Nope, don't think I will ever see that either.<br>
<br>
So, the point of all of this, and in complete relation to this post is to find a way to make wizards at least a bit more attractive to groups than they are...and this is what Verant wants, more grouping (they even come right out and say it with their new patch in test).  <br>
<br>
I ask you, besides the oft unseen direct damage, what do we have to offer.  If a tree falls in the woods, and nobody is there to hear it, does it really make a sound?<br>
